						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the Karivaradarāja-perumāḻ temple.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription describes the king (name lost) as <hi rend="italic">Parakēsarivarman Tribhu ••• •••</hi> and seems to record a gift for offerings. The other details are lost.</p>						

